## Quick Start

### 1. Wrap your app with `CustomPushProvider`

```tsx
// App.tsx or main.tsx
import { CustomPushProvider } from './push-notification/pushProvider'

function App() {
  return (
    <CustomPushProvider
      onToast={(msg) => {
        // Show in-app toast when tab is active
        // Plug in your toast library here (react-hot-toast, sonner, etc.)
        console.log('Toast:', msg.title, msg.body)
      }}
    >
      <YourApp />
    </CustomPushProvider>
  )
}
```

### 2. Request permission from a button click

```tsx
import { usePushMessage } from './push-notification/usePushMessage'

function EnableNotifications() {
  const { requestPermission, isPermissionGranted, browserSupport } = usePushMessage()

  if (!browserSupport.isSupported) {
    return <p>{browserSupport.reason}</p>
  }

  return (
    <button onClick={() => requestPermission()}>
      {isPermissionGranted ? '✓ Notifications enabled' : 'Enable notifications'}
    </button>
  )
}
```

> **⚠ Safari requires** `requestPermission()` to be called from a **user gesture**
> (button click). It will silently fail if called automatically.

### 3. Access messages and token

```tsx
import { usePushMessage } from './push-notification/usePushMessage'

function NotificationBell() {
  const { messages, token, clearMessages } = usePushMessage()

  return (
    <div>
      <span>{messages.length} new</span>
      <div>
        {messages.map(msg => (
          <div key={msg.id}>
            <strong>{msg.title}</strong>
            <p>{msg.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <button onClick={clearMessages}>Clear</button>
    </div>
  )
}
```

