## Service Worker

The service worker file (`{{SW_FILENAME}}`) must be in your `public/` directory.
It handles background push notifications and notification click redirects.

- **Vite**: `public/{{SW_FILENAME}}`
- **Next.js**: `public/{{SW_FILENAME}}`

---

## Safari Notes

| Feature | Chrome/Firefox | Safari 16+ | Safari < 16 |
|---------|---------------|------------|-------------|
| Web Push | ✓ | ✓ (VAPID only) | ✗ Not supported |
| Auto-permission | ✓ | ✗ Requires user gesture | ✗ |
| FCM Direct | ✓ | ✗ Use VAPID | ✗ |
| Notification click | `client.navigate()` | `clients.openWindow()` fallback | N/A |

---

## How it Works

- **Tab is active** → `onToast` callback fires → show in-app toast
- **Tab is inactive / different tab** → native push notification appears
- **Notification clicked** → service worker redirects to the URL in the payload

